        <abstract>
            <p>ARW’s simple explanation of dimorphic forms is satisfactory.</p>
            <p>On "non-blending" of certain varieties, CD thinks ARW has not understood him. He does not refer to fertility. He crossed two differently coloured varieties of peas and "got both varieties perfect, but none intermediate". Something like this must occur in ARW’s butterflies.</p>
        </abstract>
